The Department of Social Development has reported a teen marriage after the rape and kidnapping of an 15-year-old Ngonyameni orphan. This came after the social worker led an investigation recently. It is reported that the social worker was renewing the child support grant, when the social worker was informed that the teen had been married against her will. The social worker immediately contacted the Amangwe SAPS. It was reported that the teen was kidnapped from her home and taken to the suspects residence in Ngonyameni, where she was held against her will and repeatedly raped. Police said that the family of the suspect had gone to the homestead of the orphan to negotiate lobola. Both families agreed on seven heads of cattle to be paid. A case of kidnapping and rape is being investigated by the Estcourt FCS.